<m0>THE STOCK MARKET<ql>
<m1><ue5><styl>hed,18p,18,1,jam<ql>
<m0>Dow ends session lower<ql>
<m1><ue5><m4>   LINE 1 IS 3.84 PICA(S) SHORT<m2><ql>
<m4>   TOTAL HEAD DEPTH IS .323 INCHES<m2><ql>
<ql>
<m1><styl>txt,18p<ql>
<ep>
<m0>   Late bargain-hunting helped stocks recover part of their losses Monday, but the broad market ended mostly lower as underlying concerns deepened about rising interest rates and inflation.<ep>
   The Dow Jones industrial average fell 13.72 points to 5,464.31, rebounding from a loss of 55 earlier in the afternoon. <m1> <m0>The blue-chip index (--) which lost about 90 points last week as new signs of strong economic growth aggravated concerns about inflation and sent long-term interest rates above 7 percent (--) has now fallen 4 percent from its all-time high set just over a month ago.<ep>
   Most broader blue-chip measures were lower too. But in keeping with the recent trend, those indexes dominated by more speculative issues managed some small gains after a late rebound. The Nasdaq composite index gained 1.71 to 1,186.31 and the Russell 2000 list of smaller companies rose 0.02 to 346.87.<ep>
